<h1>Lifestyle Evagelism</h1>
<p>Another means which every Christian has at his or her disposal for witnessing is Lifestyle Evangelism.</p>
<h2>Lifestyle Evangelism</h2>
<p>Lifestyle Evangelism is a life-sharing, life-giving evangelism which includes a verbal sharing of what Christ means in a person's life. Lifestyle Evangelism is an expression of one's faith that begins with the new birth experience and ends with the last breath.</p>
<p>It is a commitment. A person has to make a total commitment to Christ. Once they do, they commit themselves to everything Christ is and stands for. They begin to act with sensitivity and understanding.</p>
<p>Every Christian is a witness, be it a winning and willing witness, or a reluctant witness.</p>
<h3>Every Member Evangelism</h3>
<p>Lifestyle Evangelism is every Christian being a witness to Jesus Christ.</p>
<h3>Every Day Evangelism</h3>
<p>Lifestyle Evangelism is the rank-and-file Christians witnessing every day in their natural, normal daily contacts and relationships.</p>
<h3>Everywhere Evangelism</h3>
<p>Lifestyle Evangelism has no special place where it is practiced. It can be done anywhere, anytime, by any Christian. Jesus was doing lifestyle evangelism when He introduced the woman of Samaria to living water beside Jacob's well (see John 4).</p>
<h3>Demonstration Evangelism</h3>
<p>Lifestyle Evangelism is to live in a way that what we are speaks as loudly as what we say.</p>
<p>Lifestyle Evangelism is "show and tell" evangelism. It is witnessing in such a way that one's own lifestyle endeavors to be a living example of God's intention for humanity.</p>
<h3>Body Evangelism</h3>
<p>Lifestyle Evangelism is "Body Evangelism". It is concerned with building up the body of Christ, the church.</p>
<p>Lifestyle Evangelism seeks to relate the convert to the church. It seeks to help persons find their place in that mystical body of Christ and in a local body of believers.</p>
<p>Lifestyle Evangelism is body evangelism in the sense that it involves every member of the body of Christ.</p>
<p>Lifestyle Evangelism sees the church as a body gifted by the Holy Trinity with the necessary spiritual gifts to build up the body of Christ in the world.</p>
<p>Lifestyle Evangelism is not only body evangelism in the sense of bodybuilding and spiritual gifts, but also in that we also offer our very own bodies as a living sacrifice to Christ. Lifestyle evangelism begins with the death to self and the offering of our own bodies to Christ in His service.</p>
<p>[scripture quote] The fruit of the righteous is a tree of life; and he that winneth souls is wise. Proverbs 11:30</p>

